{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Anticipated questions + back-pocket answers\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Q: How does Granola pick the \u8220"one thing\u8221"?} > The portfolio is five categories (Section 5 of the brief \u8212- A/B/C/D/E). Per meeting Granola ranks them by how strongly the data supports a real surprise, and picks the top one. If nothing clears the bar, the Brief is just \u8220"the room\u8221" \u8212- which is the deliberate quiet-over-comprehensive design.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Q: What about Pat \u8212- would they be offended you didn\u8217't invite them?} > The action is {\i Ping Pat for a quick read} \u8212- a draft, never sent. You decide whether to send. It\u8217's Pat-aware, not Pat-bypassing.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Q: Is this just chat with a different UI?} > No.\u160 ?Chat is the user asking. The Brief is Granola surfacing one thing \u8212- unprompted, at the moment it matters. It\u8217's the inverse direction.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Q: Why not three modules / a sidebar tab?} > Section 10 of the brief \u8212- modules make the user {\i look for} the org intel Granola has. The Brief flips that: one load-bearing thing at the moment the user needs it, then it gets out of the way.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Q: What happens if Granola is wrong?} > The micro-actions are designed for cheap retreat. {\i Bring this up} is undoable. The pinned bullet is dismissable on hover. {\i Ping Pat} never sends. The only cost of a bad surface is two seconds of attention.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Q: Why does the recording notification say \u8220"Chrome\u8221"?} > That\u8217's the existing Granola notification \u8212- it surfaces when Granola detects a meeting in your browser. The Brief reuses it (Beat 2 of the arc), only the copy carries forward the prep \u8212- see Section 12 of the brief: \u8220"visually indistinguishable from today\u8217's Granola recording notification except for the appended bring-up copy.\u8221"\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
